  "prompt": "Without any external help, how many pennies can you stack before the tower collapses?",
  "response": "Stacking pennies into a tower without any external support can be quite challenging due to their small size and smooth surfaces. In practice, most people find it difficult to stack more than 2 or 3 pennies before they topple over. \n\nHowever, with a very steady hand and a lot of patience, some individuals have reportedly managed to stack up to 10 or slightly more in ideal conditions. The Guinness World Record for the tallest stack of pennies, set by Alex Todd in 2016, is 1,000 pennies, but this was done with the aid of a stabilizing device.\n\nWithout any external help, achieving a stack of more than 5 pennies would be considered exceptional.",
